definitions: rising in revolt against established government or authority to challenge control
showing an upward rushing movement like waves or tide flowing forcefully upward
examples: The insurgent forces captured several government buildings
Insurgent groups organized protests against the new law
The insurgent waves crashed violently against the seawall
Steam rose in insurgent billows from the hot springs

definitions: too great to be overcome, surmounted, or solved regardless of effort or resources applied
examples: The team faced insurmountable obstacles in completing the project
Language barriers proved insurmountable for the new immigrants

definitions: remaining complete and whole without any part removed, broken, or damaged
examples: The ancient vase remained intact despite the earthquake
Her reputation emerged intact from the investigation

definitions: lacking physical substance and unable to be touched or grasped with hands
difficult to define, understand, or pin down precisely due to abstract nature
examples: Love is an intangible force that binds people together
The company's intangible assets include patents and trademarks
There was an intangible feeling of unease in the room
Success depends on many intangible factors like timing

definitions: necessary to make something complete or forming an essential part of whole
relating to or denoting integers or performed using integration in mathematics
examples: Exercise is integral to maintaining good health
Trust forms an integral part of any relationship
The integral calculus exam covered definite and indefinite integrals
Students solved integral equations using various mathematical methods

definitions: having various parts or aspects linked or coordinated into unified functioning whole
examples: The school developed an integrated curriculum across all subjects
Modern smartphones offer integrated cameras and computing systems

definitions: serving to integrate or tending to combine separate elements into coordinated whole
examples: Integrative medicine combines traditional and alternative healing approaches
The company adopted an integrative approach to problem solving

definitions: able to be understood or comprehended clearly by the mind or senses
examples: Her handwriting was barely intelligible after writing so quickly
The professor made complex theories intelligible to first-year students

definitions: planned, meant, or designed for a particular purpose or person deliberately
examples: The gift was intended as a surprise for her birthday
These instructions are intended for advanced users only

definitions: increased in degree, strength, or severity to become more acute or pronounced
examples: The storm intensified as it moved toward the coast
Security measures were intensified after the threat warning

definitions: increasing in strength, degree, or severity in an ongoing or progressive manner
examples: The intensifying heat made outdoor work nearly impossible
Intensifying competition forced companies to innovate constantly

definitions: involving or using great effort, energy, or resources in concentrated thorough manner
examples: The patient required intensive care after the accident
Students attended an intensive language course over summer

definitions: done deliberately with conscious design or purpose rather than by accident
examples: The damage appeared to be intentional rather than accidental
She made an intentional effort to include everyone

definitions: allowing continuous two-way transfer of information or mutual action between participants
examples: The museum features interactive exhibits for children to explore
Modern classrooms use interactive whiteboards for dynamic lessons

definitions: able to be used in place of each other without making any difference
examples: The parts are interchangeable between different model cars
In this recipe, honey and maple syrup are interchangeable

definitions: existing, carried on, or participating between different colleges or their students
examples: She competed in intercollegiate swimming championships every year
The debate team participates in intercollegiate tournaments nationwide

definitions: having different parts or elements connected or related to each other mutually
examples: Global economies are increasingly interconnected through trade networks
The body's systems are interconnected and affect each other

definitions: extending, existing, or traveling between different continents across oceanic distances
examples: The airline offers intercontinental flights to six continents
Intercontinental ballistic missiles can reach targets across oceans

definitions: depending on each other for support, function, or meaning in reciprocal relationship
examples: The ecosystem contains interdependent species that rely on each other
Modern nations are interdependent through global supply chains

definitions: relating to or involving different religions or members of different religious groups
examples: The community center hosts interfaith dialogue sessions monthly
An interfaith marriage requires understanding and respect

definitions: preventing something from continuing or being carried out properly by getting involved
examples: The interfering neighbor constantly complained about normal activities
Radio signals were interfering with the aircraft communications

definitions: existing, occurring, or traveling between different galaxies in outer space
examples: Scientists study intergalactic space to understand dark matter
The novel featured intergalactic travel between distant civilizations

definitions: serving temporarily or for the time being until permanent arrangement is made
examples: An interim manager was appointed while searching continued
The committee issued an interim report on their findings

definitions: crossed or woven together in an alternating pattern like threads or fingers
examples: The basket showed beautifully interlaced strips of bamboo
Their interlaced fingers showed the couple's deep connection

definitions: crossing or weaving together in alternating pattern to form unified structure
examples: The interlacing branches formed a natural canopy overhead
Video uses interlacing techniques to display smooth motion

definitions: fitting together tightly by having parts that connect or engage with each other
examples: The puzzle pieces had interlocking edges for secure fit
Interlocking directorates linked the major corporations together

definitions: coming between two things in time, place, order, character, or degree
examples: She enrolled in intermediate Spanish after completing beginner level
The intermediate stage of development shows mixed characteristics

definitions: occurring at irregular intervals with periods of stopping and starting repeatedly
examples: The region experiences intermittent rainfall throughout the year
She suffered from intermittent headaches for several months

definitions: advocating or practicing cooperation and understanding between nations over isolationism
examples: The internationalist perspective emphasizes global collaboration on climate
His internationalist views shaped foreign policy for decades

definitions: destructive to both sides in a conflict, especially within a group
examples: The party was weakened by internecine conflicts between factions
Internecine warfare devastated the region for generations

definitions: able to operate in conjunction with other systems or organizations effectively
capable of exchanging and using information between different computer systems
examples: Emergency services need interoperable communication systems for coordination
The military requires interoperable equipment among allied forces
Software developers create interoperable programs that share data
Cloud platforms offer interoperable services across different providers

definitions: relating to relationships or communication between people in social interactions
examples: Strong interpersonal skills are essential for team leadership
Therapy helped improve their interpersonal relationship dynamics

definitions: existing, occurring, or traveling between different planets within a solar system
examples: NASA plans interplanetary missions to Mars and beyond
Interplanetary dust affects spacecraft during long journeys

definitions: relating to or providing an interpretation or explanation of something's meaning
examples: The dancer gave an interpretative performance of the music
Museums use interpretative displays to explain historical artifacts

definitions: having been explained, understood, or translated from one form to another
examples: The ancient text was interpreted by linguistic experts
Her silence was interpreted as agreement by others

definitions: designed to explain the meaning or significance of something to audiences
examples: Park rangers provide interpretive tours of historical sites
The museum hired interpretive guides for school groups

definitions: existing between or involving people of different races or ethnic backgrounds
examples: Interracial marriages have become more common and accepted
The school promotes interracial understanding through cultural programs

definitions: placed in a grave or tomb with formal or ceremonial burial rites
examples: The president was interred at Arlington National Cemetery
Ancient pharaohs were interred with treasures and servants

definitions: having mutual or reciprocal relation or connection between different elements
examples: Climate change involves many interrelated environmental factors
The course examines interrelated themes in world literature

definitions: having the force or form of a question to seek information
denoting a word or construction used in asking questions grammatically
examples: She spoke in an interrogative tone throughout the interview
His interrogative manner made witnesses feel uncomfortable
Students learned interrogative pronouns like who, what, and where
The interrogative sentence structure requires specific word order

definitions: stopped or broken into by something that prevents continuation temporarily
examples: Their conversation was interrupted by a phone call
The power outage interrupted work for several hours

definitions: existing or conducted between different schools or involving students from multiple schools
examples: The interscholastic chess tournament attracted hundreds of students
She excelled in interscholastic debate competitions statewide

definitions: meeting and crossing at a point to form an angle or junction
examples: The intersecting lines formed a perfect right angle
Their intersecting career paths led to collaboration

definitions: existing or carried on between different states within a country
examples: Interstate commerce regulations affect trucking companies nationwide
They traveled on interstate highways across the country

definitions: occurring or situated between stars in a galaxy or universe
examples: Interstellar space contains vast amounts of dust and gas
The probe entered interstellar space beyond our solar system

definitions: existing or occurring between different tribes or tribal groups
examples: Intertribal councils work to resolve disputes peacefully
The powwow celebrates intertribal unity and cultural sharing

definitions: occurring in the time or space between two things or events
examples: Many changes occurred during the intervening years
The intervening mountains blocked radio signals effectively

definitions: blended or combined together so closely that separation becomes difficult
examples: Their lives became interwoven through shared experiences
The plot features interwoven storylines from multiple characters

definitions: dying without having made a valid will for property distribution
relating to inheritance when someone dies without leaving a valid will
examples: He died intestate, causing legal complications for heirs
The intestate succession laws determined property distribution
Intestate estates follow state laws for asset distribution
Lawyers specialize in handling intestate inheritance cases

definitions: relating to or affecting the intestines in the digestive system
examples: The patient suffered from intestinal inflammation requiring treatment
Intestinal bacteria play important roles in human health
